# CHANGELOG is append-only: every PR adds bullets under `### [Unreleased]`, so
# concurrent PRs touch the same lines and collide. The built-in `union` merge
# driver resolves these by keeping BOTH sides' added lines instead of writing
# conflict markers — honored by local merge/rebase and by GitHub's merge button
# (it is a built-in driver, not a custom one needing per-clone git config).
#
# This is safe only because a persistent `### [Unreleased]` heading always lives
# in CHANGELOG.md (see AUTHORING.md → "CHANGELOG & versioning"): PRs add bullets
# under it but never recreate the heading, so union never duplicates it. The
# release skill leaves a fresh empty `### [Unreleased]` behind after each cut,
# and check_changelog.py fails the build if the heading is ever duplicated.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
